The amount of evaporation is usually assessed using potential evapotranspiration (PET). To determine the nominal evaporation rate in India, PET was calculated for 50 meteorological stations all over India using the available meteorological data from 1981 to 2020. The PET rate was calculated using the Penman–Monteith method, the standard method for calculating the evaporation rate. The following expression was used to find the PET of the selected stations in India (Rao et al. 2012):1ETo=0.408ΔRn-G+γ900T+273u2es-eaΔ+γ1+0.34u2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
